     <div type="to_the_reader">
   <head>To the Reader.</head>
   <p>
      <seg rend="decorInit">H</seg>Earing how fast this Sermon hath
vttered, and yet how miserably
it hath bene abused in printing,
as it were with whole limmes
cut off at once, and cleane left
out, I haue taken a little paines
(as my sicknesse gaue me leaue) both to perfect
the matter, and to correct the print. Now as the
Angell said to Iohn,<note place="margin">Reu. 10. 10.</note>
      <hi>Take this booke and eate
it,</hi> so I wish that thou hadst so digested this do<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ctrine,
that all the parts of thy bodie and soule
were strengthened by it. But if all this will not
make thee content with that thou hast, sorrowe
that thy couetousnesse is greater then others: and
neuer loue thy selfe vntill thou canst find in thy
hart to be blessed. Farewell.</p>
   <closer>
      <signed>Thine H. Smith.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
